Victoria Azarenka wiki, net worth, son, husband and salary Victoria Fyodorovna Azarenka AKA Victoria Azarenka was born on 31st July 1989 in Minsk, Byelorussian SSR, in the Soviet Union. She is the daughter of Alla and Fedor Azarenka. She was born in a middle-class family and has an elder brother Max. She is of Belarusian nationality and can fluently speak Belarusian, Russian and English. She started playing tennis at the age of seven years old when her mother was working at a tennis club. Her mother gave her a racket and suggested her to hit the ball against a wall to keep her out of trouble. Soon, Azarenka started to play tennis professionally. She played her main match in the year 2003. Then in 2005, she won the Junior Australian Open and the Junior U.S. Open, and became successful to be named an ITF junior title holder. Same year, she also won her first ITF Women’s Circuit title in Luxembourg. Following year, she came to the WTA’s Top 100 rundown. In the year 2009, she won the Brisbane International title against Marion Bartoli. She got the 6th high school female singles champion in the occasion’s history in the wake of beating Serena Williams in the last at the Sony Ericsson Open in Miami. She won the Bank of the West Classic in 2010 and the Sony Ericsson Open in 2011. Azarenka moved to No. 3 after the U.S. Open. In 2012, she won the ninth WTA title at Sydney and on 30th January 2012, she bounced from No. 3 to No.1. She captured her second in a row Australian Open title in January 2013 and went ahead to the last of U.S. Open.
